  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: if you block and unblock a user, it will be added automatically to your contact list on app, but technically user is not your contact, because he can't see your custom name. So after blocking and unlocking user, you can't add it to contacts normally to share your profile data.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nuser B  is not in your contact list; can see \"Add to contact\" in 1-1 with user B\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nuser B is in your contact list, but in fact he is not (he can't see your custom name) \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- User A: create 1-1 chat with User B, don't add him to your contacts\r\n- User A: exchange several  messages with user B\r\n- User A: block user B\r\n- User A: unblock User B\r\n- User B: send several message to user A\r\n- User A: check contact list and 1-1 chat with user B\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: release 0.10.0\r\n* Operating System: Android, IOS\r\n",
